reviews.text:
We've lived here 7 years and somehow never ate at 404 Kitchen. What a hidden gem in the middle of the Gulch. We were there on a Friday night and they weren't too busy. Our waiter was fantastic. The food was on par with the best restaurants in Nashville and better than most.

AND unlike most restaurants in Nashville the seats were comfortable and it wasn't too loud.

We will definitely be back!

I always enjoy my meals here! We went on a weeknight and there was two of us and we both very much enjoyed our dinner. They also probably have one of the best bourbon selections in downtown Nashville, certainly in The Gulch
For some reason this place wasn‚Äôt busy. Wine list could be improved. Pork belly was just ok. Otherwise, food was very good. Shrimp and grits, blondie, short rib and duck breast all solid.

We are foodies and have had 404 on our list for a while. We finally got the chance to go and we‚Äôre not disappointed! Colton Cahill, the chef, and wait staff were professional and timely. We tried about everything we could handle and must say the flavors we on point! The dining room was comfortable and wasn‚Äôt loud either. Be sure and get their Old Fashioned, it was wonderful! Be sure you don‚Äôt miss their dessert selection!

The 404 Kitchen was absolute best choice for dinner. I googled restaurants in Nashville that had a good bourbon/whiskey selection, and I kept going back to this listing. I‚Äôm so glad we did!! The service was warm and wonderful. The food was unique and so good! Ah, but the drinks!!! Whiskey Under the Bridge was such a great twist on a hotty toddy, almost crossed with an old fashioned. We loved it so much. We also tried a 10 year Pappy for the first time, and it was out of this world. We will definitely come back! The 404 Kitchen is a destination!!

editorial_summary.overview: Farm-to-table New American fare & craft cocktails are served in a chic digs, plus a basement bar.

detailedReviews.text: I was so looking forward to this but sadly disappointed. We started with the beet salad and scallop toast, then tried the catfish bites and shrimp risotto. The beet salad was so salty, I didn‚Äôt even finish it and the catfish was too bland, more of a chicken nugget flavor and soggy. The cocktails were wonderful, just wished the meal was better. That being said, many others rave about their meals, maybe my expectations were too high.

detailedReviews.author: Randi Jo
detailedReviews.text: The 404 Kitchen was absolute best choice for dinner. I googled restaurants in Nashville that had a good bourbon/whiskey selection, and I kept going back to this listing. I‚Äôm so glad we did!! The service was warm and wonderful. The food was unique and so good! Ah, but the drinks!!! Whiskey Under the Bridge was such a great twist on a hotty toddy, almost crossed with an old fashioned. We loved it so much. We also tried a 10 year Pappy for the first time, and it was out of this world. We will definitely come back! The 404 Kitchen is a destination!!

detailedReviews.author: Misty Blu Stewart
detailedReviews.text:
This is one of Nashville‚Äôs few remaining independent venues. Full of creativity and intention. Most of Nashville‚Äôs nicer restaurant options are all revamped chains or secondary locations of a larger corporate venue. So it‚Äôs super special to have this venue in nashville. The whiskey library and society in Gertie‚Äôs is phenomenal. JOIN and GET YOURSELF A LOCKER!!!  the bar staff is thoughtful, creative and super knowledgeable . Shout out to JOHNNIE! the management team always remembers your name and greets you with sincerity! Shout out to SHIRLEY!!!! the service team is so kind and you really get the best service in town‚Ä¶ RACHEL AND KAHLIL!

The live music on Wednesday and Thursday nights, the creative themed cocktail menus, the artwork, the vibes‚Ä¶ all amazing.

I love that the whiskey bar is downstairs and restaurant is upstairs- it allows for a good separation between the loud exciting speakeasy and an elevated intimate dinner.

Their annual DERBY event and WHISKEY PAIRING dinners are amazing also - don‚Äôt miss them

detailedReviews.author: Wes
detailedReviews.text: Great food, great service and never disappoints. I must dinning experience if you are in Nashville.

detailedReviews.author: Curtis Scafe
detailedReviews.text: Great food and great vibe. Lobster Mac is my favorite but everything is good!

detailedReviews.author: Nick Gentry

We've lived here 7 years and somehow never ate at 404 Kitchen. What a hidden gem in the middle of the Gulch. We were there on a Friday night and they weren't too busy. Our waiter was fantastic. The food was on par with the best restaurants in Nashville and better than most.

AND unlike most restaurants in Nashville the seats were comfortable and it wasn't too loud.

We will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Nahma Nadich

detailedReviews.author: Bonnie Murray

I had the salmon dish which was good, but the broth a little too salty. My hubby loved the pork chop dish and highly recommends it.  Their cornbread is a must have appetizer.

detailedReviews.text:
Service was off the charts.

detailedReviews.text: I was visiting from out of town and hosted clients for dinner - everything was fantastic. Our service was perfect with amazing suggestions and a personal feel. My only complaint is that I do not live in Nashville and cannot come back more.

detailedReviews.author: Katie Kerchner
detailedReviews.text: Wonderful dinner/reunion with colleagues. Food was beautiful and delicious. Matt Bolus is doing amazing things at 404 Kitchen!

detailedReviews.author: Lori Heim
detailedReviews.text: We love this restaurant and always make a reservation when we are in town.  10/10!!

detailedReviews.author: Collin Curry
detailedReviews.text: Went for brunch. More people need to come here for brunch! Atmosphere was great, server Micah was excellent, and the manager even touched base. They accommodated six people on Sunday with no issues, no wait. Their fried chicken is great.

detailedReviews.author: Alexis Bush
detailedReviews.text: The food was excellent! We had a large party, which definitely slowed down service, and some members of our party received the wrong food, but we didn‚Äôt mind too much! Such a great atmosphere and our server was very personable. Would definitely go back!

detailedReviews.author: Michael Allison
detailedReviews.text: Always an amazing experience.  The staff was so accommodating in my reservation.  I can always rely on 404 Kitchen getting me in.  Awesome food!

detailedReviews.author: isabelle goodrich
detailedReviews.text: I have literally never had a worse restaurant experience. My mother and I got AN HOUR LONG political lecture from our server. Completely unwarranted. It was so inappropriate, unprofessional and disrespectful. My food was cold by the time he was done speaking at us. Never go here.

detailedReviews.author: Jennifer Allen
detailedReviews.text: Always a top notch experience!

detailedReviews.author: Steve Kennedy
detailedReviews.text: I always enjoy my meals here! We went on a weeknight and there was two of us and we both very much enjoyed our dinner. They also probably have one of the best bourbon selections in downtown Nashville, certainly in The Gulch

detailedReviews.author: Mark C
detailedReviews.text: So disappointing for the cost. Service was terrible, 35 mins for drinks, 50 mins to order food. Starters arrived after 90 mins. Mains after 2hours. Restaurant was empty which was baffling. Pork belly was dry and Shepherds Pie had so much pepper.

detailedReviews.author: William Hunter
detailedReviews.text: Matt Bolus has created an epic eatery in the Gulch. From the bolognese to the pork chop to the crackers (yes they are deep fried) are must eats. Get to 404 Kitchen as fast as you can.

detailedReviews.author: G Gintz
detailedReviews.text: Our server Katherine and the chef were working over time to make sure I had a safe dining experience. They went over every menu item to make sure I could eat it safely without having an allergic reaction. The food was outstanding. I would drive from out of town to dine at The 404 kitchen. Every single menu item we chose was the best I've eaten.

detailedReviews.author: Angelica Nery
detailedReviews.text: They were good. They were very busy so food took long to arrive. Really good food!

detailedReviews.author: Julie Witkowski
detailedReviews.text: So good. Comfortable atmosphere. Wonderful dishes not over sized.

detailedReviews.author: E Ry
detailedReviews.text:
Disappointing Decline at 404 Kitchen

We‚Äôve visited 404 Kitchen a couple of times before and had fantastic experiences‚Äîthanks in large part to Moses and Colton. Their professionalism, attentiveness, and the quality of service they provided made our meals truly memorable. The food and drinks on those visits were equally impressive.

Unfortunately, our most recent visit was a complete letdown. Neither Moses nor Colton were working, and the difference was immediately noticeable. Service was unorganized and inattentive. Our server had an overwhelming body odor, which made the dining experience uncomfortable. We were served small sodas without any offer of refills, and the food itself was bland and uninspired‚Äînowhere near the level we previously enjoyed.

Adding to the disappointment, a woman who appeared to be in a managerial role was making rounds to other tables, but she completely ignored ours. This was particularly frustrating, as we were hoping to share feedback directly and give the restaurant a chance to address our concerns.

Sadly, this visit has caused us to reconsider returning to 404 Kitchen. The inconsistency in service and quality is too significant to overlook, and it‚Äôs unfortunate to see such a promising restaurant falter so dramatically.

detailedReviews.author: Staci McKeegan
detailedReviews.text:
We went for Mother's Day brunch with our parents. We've always heard good things about 404 so decided to try it. We had a reservation for 6 and were seated quickly but it went downhill from there. Our server finally greeted us and took our drink order. They came 20 minutes later, cokes coffee and tea nothing from the bar. We were told the cokes were in bottles so no free refills. Weird comment but ok. The cokes came in small glasses and watered down but whatever. Our food took an hour and 15 to come out, we barely saw our server during this time as we all sat with empty drinks and water. When the food finally arrived it was luke warm, obvious it had been prepared and sitting for quite some time. My 84 year old father-in-law ordered the Omelette and never dreamed the peppers in it were jalape√±o peppers. It would have been nice if he was warned. He asked for milk to cool his mouth and it took awhile to come out.
There were plenty of people working, they weren't short staffed. We were just trying to figure out what all the staff walking around were doing.
Our families were happy they had plenty of time to catch up so that was nice, but me and my husband were very disappointed. I was surprised there were no apologies for the wait, service or the food issue. I never write reviews but this was such a terrible experience.
On our way out someone commented that Gertie's looked cute. I asked the downstairs hostess what time it opened. She just shrugged her shoulders...summed up our experience pretty well.

detailedReviews.author: Will Andrews
detailedReviews.text: Went for Mother's day brunch. Salads arrived within 5 minutes of ordering but we waited almost 40 minutes on our entrees. Although the food was pretty good, the wait killed the entire experience. Service, service, service. Unfortunately we wont be back.

detailedReviews.author: Dula Love
detailedReviews.text: The food was good and wait staff was friendly, however it took 2 1/2 hours for everyone to get served their main course with one of us not getting it until 25 minutes after everyone's else, and that was after the waiter said it would only be 2 minutes, it sort of ruined the experience. And we wernt offered a single apology for it. Very disappointed in their service timing.

detailedReviews.author: Stu Cohn
detailedReviews.text: We hosted a dinner for 12 people at 404 Kitchen Nashville.  Both the food and service were outstanding.  The staff is very professional and attentive.  The space is most welcoming. Highly recommended.

detailedReviews.author: Eric Michaud
detailedReviews.text:
This place had great service and very good atmosphere.  We were on the patio a group of 12.

This is higher end and designed for sharing.  The portion sizes were bigger than they said (tri tip easily feed 4 of us).  You get what you pay for, it was high quality and great tasting food, and priced accordingly.

Also has a great whiskey collection and one of the best gluten free menus.

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Griffin
detailedReviews.text: First round of drinks took a while to come out and the server never came back. He was too busy dealing with a kitchen staff that refused to cook. Table next to us had been waiting over 2 hours to get their food that was not going to come. Eventually we walked out.

detailedReviews.author: Stephanie Cochoff
detailedReviews.text:
This place was horrid. The place was packed, no one had food on their tables, servers weren‚Äôt providing updates as to what was going on or even keeping drinks on the table, etc. they were out of water glasses for the first 20 min after we were seated. our server forgot to put our order in and told me 30 min later that they were out of entree I‚Äôd ordered. Other customers were so mad that they were getting loud with the servers.

Ultimately, we left before the food came out because the table next to us said they‚Äôd been waiting for 2.5 hours.

This place was falling apart. I‚Äôm surprised they are still in business at all.

detailedReviews.author: Phil Ledwith
detailedReviews.text: Waited two hours for food that never came. Our server avoided us and gave no updates. Absolutely unacceptable experience ‚Äî won‚Äôt be returning

detailedReviews.author: Karl Martin
detailedReviews.text: Wir sind auf einer Rundreise durch den S√ºden aber so schlecht gegessen wie hier haben wir noch nicht. Es wird viel zu fett gekocht und zum Dip gibt es nur salzige Cracker. Bier ist aus der Dose.

detailedReviews.author: Lauren McGrath
detailedReviews.text: I wrote a lengthier review about our 2025 New Year‚Äôs Eve dining experience, but it seems to have disappeared. In short, the food was not good, the service was terrible, and it was a missed opportunity for a good meal in a city filled with amazing food. I wish I took the time to share my feedback in person.

detailedReviews.author: Grant Robarts
detailedReviews.text:
I have dined twice at The 404 Kitchen and both times have been exceptional! My first experience was in October of 2023 & the food, service & atmosphere was phenomenal.

Most recently I booked a celebration dinner with their events manager Doss for 21 people! It couldn‚Äôt have been an easier experience, the food & service was impeccable! The servers we had were unbelievable in their approach of keeping out of the way while maintaining a happy room of 21 guests.

Whether you‚Äôre looking to enjoy an intimate dinner experience or a larger dinner party, you won‚Äôt be disappointed at The 404 Kitchen!!

detailedReviews.author: michael heim
detailedReviews.text: A gem in Nashville, vibe, food and service, all outstanding. The Gnudi was literally one of the best meals I have ever had.

detailedReviews.author: Brenda Corbin
detailedReviews.text: Food is always good. Service was great

detailedReviews.author: Madison Maillot
detailedReviews.text: My mom and I went for dinner tonight and everything including our waiter David was so wonderful!! We ordered a couple appetizers and the filet with Brussels sprouts and twice baked potatoes and they were all so delicious! David made the dinner even better by being so friendly and personable the whole time!  I will definitely be visiting this restaurant next time I visit nashville and will be requesting David be our waiter if he's working.

detailedReviews.author: James Yates (The Banditos Gun Circus)
detailedReviews.text: We are foodies and have had 404 on our list for a while. We finally got the chance to go and we‚Äôre not disappointed! Colton Cahill, the chef, and wait staff were professional and timely. We tried about everything we could handle and must say the flavors we on point! The dining room was comfortable and wasn‚Äôt loud either. Be sure and get their Old Fashioned, it was wonderful! Be sure you don‚Äôt miss their dessert selection!

detailedReviews.author: Tracy Yates
detailedReviews.text:
Our recent Sunday outing at 404 in the Gulch was nothing short of spectacular! A handful of friends who share a passion for good food and great bourbon, we were excited about the vibrant atmosphere and an impressive bar stocked with an extensive selection of liquors and wines. To say we were not disappointed would be an understatement!

As bourbon enthusiasts, we were thrilled by the unparalleled bourbon selection‚Äîtruly the best we've ever encountered. Our experience was elevated by the amazing manager, Colton Cayhill, and the attentive wait staff, who went above and beyond to ensure our night was memorable.

The true star of the evening was the chef, whose culinary artistry was evident in every dish. Each plate was a masterpiece, beautifully presented and crafted with care. The sides were thoughtfully paired with the entrees, enhancing the overall experience without overshadowing the main attractions. The portion sizes were just perfect‚Äînot too little to leave you wanting more, yet not so much that you felt overwhelmed. It was a balanced dining experience that left us completely satisfied.

We started our culinary journey with a delightful tasting of every appetizer, and the unique catfish bites were hands down our favorite! Their crispy exterior and flavorful filling made them an absolute standout. From crisp Brussels sprouts to fresh oysters and their incredible homemade crackers, each dish was a fantastic introduction to what was to come.

For our entrees, we savored duck, pork chops, and monkfish. The presentation was both elegant and creative, and as we shared each dish, we found it nearly impossible to choose a favorite. Each plate was spot-on, bursting with unique flavors that left us wanting more.

Just when we thought we couldn't possibly eat another bite, the dessert parade began! We were presented with one of each dessert: bourbon cake, cr√®me br√ªl√©e, blonde brownie, and a distinctive salted ice cream. As bourbon lovers, we were delighted with the expertly paired drinks that complemented each course perfectly.

404 is a gem in the Gulch that we highly recommend for anyone seeking an unforgettable dining experience. From the ambiance to the food and drink selections, everything was top-notch. We can‚Äôt wait to return! Cheers!

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Clements
detailedReviews.text:
My wife and I had a fantastic dinner this past weekend. Chef Matt Bolus really is one of the best chefs in Nashville. Serving up American/southern elevated cuisine, our experience at 404 Kitchen was fantastic.

A must have is their Tri-trip and the cornbread. Truly amazing.

If your are a whiskey lover this is also the place. I think it has 600 whiskeys and bourbons.

Our server, David, was incredible and made the experience that more enjoyable.

In short, go see this Nashville staple.

detailedReviews.author: Keerti Malavooru
detailedReviews.text: Good place for a large gathering

detailedReviews.author: Russ Stryker
detailedReviews.text: 404 was incredible.  Highly recommend.  David made our night.  Definitely ask for him.  Food and drinks were amazing.   Atmosphere was perfect.   Hidden Gem.  Definitely best restaurant we went to in Nashville.

detailedReviews.author: James P
detailedReviews.text: OMG! First time visiting we shared a appetizer and a dessert and I am so impressed from the building, music, food, and service was top notch! We were greeted by our server Moses explained the menu and drinks.... explained what some of the fancy words were on the menu. We shared the spinach artichoke dip which really hit! The butter pecan ice cream is to die for! Next time we are in Nashville I will plan accordingly and will make sure to visit 404 Kitchen for actual dinner. Overall truly impressed with everything.  Good job Moses.

detailedReviews.author: Andrew Carnley
detailedReviews.text: Called multiple times to try and edit my reservation didn‚Äôt answer after six times across the span of multiple days. Got seated with my group and we‚Äôre waiting on some friends to join so we delayed our food to be brought out. However, the people that showed up 30 minutes after us got their meal and was finished by the time we got ours. Was at 2 1/2 hours before I even received my main course. Was compensated a dessert which I appreciate however, the lack of service and efficiency was very poor. Waiter may have been new but did not understand how to break apart the check had to ask multiple times for a correction.

detailedReviews.author: Shelby Rice
detailedReviews.text: Had a group event here. The steak was so peppery it was difficult to eat. The Brussel sprouts were overcooked. The rest of the food was interesting, but items I just wanted to try rather than eat much of.

detailedReviews.author: Katherine Allgood
detailedReviews.text: My party and I really enjoyed the Christmas Eve buffet.  Everything (from the salad to the dessert) was delicious.  Our waiter, David, was attentive and knowledgeable.  The service (management checked in, water glass always full) was thoughtful.  Super festive night!  I really can't wait to come back.

detailedReviews.author: Alex Seidler
detailedReviews.text: I came in yesterday evening as a first time customer, and was blown away.  The service was absolutely top notch. I was with a party of 9, and we sort of played musical chairs a bit. Our server, Rachel, handled it amazingly well - with the best attitude.  The perfect balance of being available and offering space.  All the staff appeared to genuinely love working there, which makes for a completely different experience than the contrast.  The food was also top notch.  I ordered Matty's Melt, and had one of the best burgers of my life.  All in all, a wonderful experience and absolutely wonderful environment.

detailedReviews.author: John White
detailedReviews.text: Nice restaurant. Went for brunch on a Sunday. Friendly service. Bottomless Mimosas and lobster benedict, need I say more.

detailedReviews.author: Logan Luna
detailedReviews.text: Delicious food and amazing staff! Brandon the bartender and Colton the manager  provided excellent sevice, both very attentive and personable. The atmosphere was beautiful and the music was exactly what I like. Will definitely be spending many more evenings here in the near future.

detailedReviews.author: Cole Marjama
detailedReviews.text: Good drinks and good food from Brandon and Colton

detailedReviews.author: Cole Marjama
detailedReviews.text: Colton and Brandon have great service

detailedReviews.author: Vikes
detailedReviews.text: Brandon the bartender was a GOAT

detailedReviews.author: Allen A
detailedReviews.text: Probably the most bland food I have had in all of Tennessee.

detailedReviews.author: Ronald Bertin
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôve never been more disappointed in a meal in a very long time. We had the Thanksgiving buffet. It was terrible. The strip loin was very overcooked and tough as shoe leather. The mashed potatoes we so soupy that I thought it was a sauce. The stuffing was a gelatinous blob. I don‚Äôt think it could have started off as bread. The sweet potato was more of a dessert (think apple pie sugar and cinnamon filling but substitute sweet potato, topped with marshmallow). The green bean casserole had very little taste. The Mac and cheese was only Mac (dude, where‚Äôs the cheese?!). The rolls and cornbread were so dry and overcooked that they were not edible. For dessert, they ran out of pecan pie. I can see why because the pumpkin pie was the worst I‚Äôve ever had. I‚Äôm not sure what the filling was made from but it was terrible. The only saving grace was the Brussels sprouts. They were prepared well and were very tasty. This restaurant is a hard pass. So disappointed because we are visiting from out of town and were looking for a wonderful Thanksgiving meal. The advertising did not live up to our experience. Please avoid 404 Kitchen if you are looking for a good value for your money. If the chef serves this type of food at a Thanksgiving buffet, I can only imagine the quality when dining with the regular menu.

detailedReviews.author: Brian McNamara
detailedReviews.text:
The Thanksgiving Meal was the Worst we had ever had, in our lives.
Lousy Turkey, Lousy Beef,
HORRIBLE  STUFFING
( worst ever ), terrible gravy,
AWFUL PUMPKIN PIE,
Disgusting Cookies.
Everything was Horrible.
Really & Truly Horrible.
Stay Away from this place, unless you like Horrible Food.

detailedReviews.author: Alisha Reeves
detailedReviews.text:
Large portions with playful taste profiles. We enjoyed the grilled oysters as the starter and it blew my mind with flavor. Our party shared the butternut squash risotto, lobster mac & cheese, and 72 hour tri tip 28oz steak for main courses. The mac & cheese was my favorite. Dessert brought the 404 bourbon cake, creme br√ªl√©e, and baked apple. Bourbon cake was a clear winner but the mixed fruit compote on the cr√®me br√ªl√©e was a pleasant surprise.
The restaurant itself appears small at first pass but it actually sprawls and has lots of private space for large parties. The decor is simple but very classy. The lights did flicker the entire time and that was very distracting and not my favorite. Our server explained that the building was over 100 years old so it has been a problem for a while. The lighting was the only issue I took with this visit. It‚Äôs a Nashville staple and should be on your visit list.

detailedReviews.author: Laura R
detailedReviews.text: I was super impressed with this place and the menu selection! Everything we ordered was fantastic! The service was top-notch, Garrett our server was a gem! We ordered the pimento cheese (You will be so happy you did the crackers are the best ever! You will have so many left over for later, taste buds will be satisfied for days!)The beet salad was so fresh and the pork chop was delectable! Legit farm to table food.

detailedReviews.author: R B
detailedReviews.text: One of the best spots in the city. Food is always outstanding, service is excellent and Matt is the man!

detailedReviews.author: Cam Buglione
detailedReviews.text: Great atmosphere, cocktails and the regular salad with citrus was fantastic. The short rib ragu (gnudi) and the cornbread were both a bit bland; service was friendly but we had to ask a busboy to get our waiter after being there for 25 mins with no one coming by except to fill water. Same thing again with wrapping dinner up and the check

detailedReviews.author: Ron Haas
detailedReviews.text: 5 stars all around. The only downside is the price, but let's be honest, you get what you pay for. The food is amazing, but you will need a refined palette to really appreciate it. The whiskey selection is top notch.

detailedReviews.author: Dani Westover
detailedReviews.text: The service was incredible. The got us seated so quickly and we were in and out under 30 minutes. We are gluten free and so we were drawn to this restaurant because they had gluten free fried chicken and cornbread. The previous reviews raved about it and so we were encouraged to try it out. Sadly, We were disappointed of the flavor of the fried chicken especially for the cost. It felt like it was missing something. The sauces helped. The Brussels sprouts were phenomenal. Like I said the service was excellent. I the food isn‚Äôt anything to write home about.

detailedReviews.author: KJ G
detailedReviews.text: Everything (pinot grigio, pimento cheese, beet salad and shrimp and grits) was great except it is too loud. We had to scream at each other to have a conversation.

detailedReviews.author: Amanda
detailedReviews.text: Holy cow! An amazing experience! We went here for our anniversary dinner and it exceeded my expectations. Entree portions were the perfect size, everything was delicious and well prepared, and orders were taken/food brought out in a timely manner. The staff was so attentive and forehead kisses to the bartender because the cocktails were so perfectly blended and creative (made a Swiftie's heart so happy)! Recommending this place to everyone I know!

detailedReviews.author: Matthew Outman
detailedReviews.text: they could take us as a walk-in at 8 o‚Äôclock, but now it‚Äôs obvious as to why.  The atmosphere was great, as  was the  location in the gulch. The food is way overpriced and the portions very small. $16 for three oysters..  I was excited to see the tri-tip on the menu and for $110 for 20 ounces prepared and $110 Would be OK if properly cooked. Was overcooked and dry and smothered and butter.  The first two6 dollar Diet Coke came out pretty quickly, but after that, the waiter disappeared for 20 minutes with no drinks at the table and a pile of empty dishes just sitting there. I finally cleared my table and walked up to request check. go accross the street to Emmy‚Äòs, but make a reservation between 630 and eight otherwise you could walk in.

detailedReviews.author: Cara Baker Davis
detailedReviews.text: Marissa took good care of us on our date! Abundant food & a beautiful space.

detailedReviews.author: Pris S
detailedReviews.text: A disgusting taste of racism. No one should ever have such an ill experience regardless of age, sex, or gender. Waitress rushes to order, a dissatisfing topping which should be added boldly to top of menu. 3 items sounded tasteful however everything that was ordered was bland, utterly unappetizing. Forced to click a star in order to post, 0 stars given from an amazingly beautiful diverse family.

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Buckley
detailedReviews.text: David is one of the best servers I've ever had. Guy knows his food and took us through the menu at a perfect pace. Highly recommend to anyone stopping in Nashville.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Kovacik
detailedReviews.text: My Wife and I attended the House of Mustaine Wine Dinner last night and had a great time. The food was delicious and the wine was fantastic.  Got to meet Dave Mustaine and his immediate family. Would definitely go again!

detailedReviews.author: Blake Dillard
detailedReviews.text: Food was great, will go back. the top deck section was really nice

detailedReviews.author: Wilson Dyal
detailedReviews.text: Came in for my fianc√©‚Äôs birthday and was treated to a wonderful experience by Brandon! He made EVERYONE at the table feel like it was their special day! One of the managers, Colton, stopped by a few times to make sure everything was going well (which is was!)

detailedReviews.author: Gloria Alaniz
detailedReviews.text: Everything about 404 Kitchen is fabulous! Our waiter Scott was pleasant, knowledgeable, and friendly. Not annoying or too overwhelming! Just enough to enjoy and visit. Cocktails were fresh and tasty. Food was just exactly what we anticipated with a mouthful of excitement for each bite.

detailedReviews.author: Mimi NP
detailedReviews.text: The food and drinks were exceptional. Our server, Brandon, was thoughtful and attentive. An all around excellent experience.

positive.author: Nick Casanova
positive.text: Stopped in for the first time and had such a great experience. Delaney took care of us and was super friendly ‚Äî plus she makes a killer cocktail! The bourbon selection is impressive, and the whole place has such a beautiful vibe. The food was excellent too ‚Äî definitely worth a visit.

positive.author: Michael Burney
positive.text: Was in town for a business trip, stopped in because of the "404" in the name as I'm from Atlanta, and glad I did so. Katherine was a fanatastic server, gave us great info and suggestions all night, esepcially on the chicken piccata and aged gin. If you get her as your server, know you're in a for great night! I will definitely be returning the next time I make it to Nashville.

positive.author: Bailee Muse
positive.text: The food was amazing!! My party was in a rush and the staff did everything they could to serve us quickly! Everyone was friendly as well!

neutral.author: Karen Kloefkorn
neutral.text: I was so looking forward to this but sadly disappointed. We started with the beet salad and scallop toast, then tried the catfish bites and shrimp risotto. The beet salad was so salty, I didn‚Äôt even finish it and the catfish was too bland, more of a chicken nugget flavor and soggy. The cocktails were wonderful, just wished the meal was better. That being said, many others rave about their meals, maybe my expectations were too high.

neutral.author: Will Andrews
neutral.text: Went for Mother's day brunch. Salads arrived within 5 minutes of ordering but we waited almost 40 minutes on our entrees. Although the food was pretty good, the wait killed the entire experience. Service, service, service. Unfortunately we wont be back.

neutral.author: Dula Love
neutral.text: The food was good and wait staff was friendly, however it took 2 1/2 hours for everyone to get served their main course with one of us not getting it until 25 minutes after everyone's else, and that was after the waiter said it would only be 2 minutes, it sort of ruined the experience. And we wernt offered a single apology for it. Very disappointed in their service timing.

negative.author: Craig
negative.text: The food was not up to part for it's price point.

negative.author: Joseph Jacobson
negative.text:
My wife and I went here tonight and the food was abysmal. Luckily the service was friendly. Our server was awesome  (ableit clearly overwhelmed) but the food was not good.

The spinach and artichoke dip was awful paired with ‚Äúfried saltines‚Äù that were so salty they were barely edible. Our entire table of 4 people all hated them.

My chicken piccata was so salty and dry I didn‚Äôt finish it and will be throwing the unfinished half away.

The cornbread was bland. Burger was decent but overpriced and everything else was simply mid.

At the end of the meal we paid $245 after having two entrees, an app, and three cocktails each.

Not even remotely worth it. This place sucked. I hate to say it but I speak emphatically because I would never want someone to go here ever.

negative.author: isabelle goodrich
negative.text: I have literally never had a worse restaurant experience. My mother and I got AN HOUR LONG political lecture from our server. Completely unwarranted. It was so inappropriate, unprofessional and disrespectful. My food was cold by the time he was done speaking at us. Never go here.
